# Help: Cryptographic algorithms (ciphers, hashes, modes, MACs)
#
# Enables the set of algorithms most test suites, filesystem
# encryption, IPsec, and VPN workloads reference: symmetric ciphers
# (AES, ChaCha20, Blowfish, Camellia, CAST5/6, Serpent, Twofish,
# 3DES/DES, ARIA), block cipher modes (CBC, CTR, GCM, CCM, XTS,
# ECB, CTS), authenticated helper (ESSIV), hashes (MD5,
# SHA1, SHA2-256/384/512, SHA3, SM3, BLAKE2b, xxHash), CRC
# (CRC32 and CRC32c), MACs (HMAC, CMAC, XCBC), asymmetric
# (RSA, DH + RFC 7919 groups, ECDH, ECDSA, ECRDSA), and Kerberos
# profile (CRYPTO_KRB5).
#
# Every symbol is tristate. Many consumers (dm-crypt, fscrypt,
# fsverity, IPsec, NFSv4 with Kerberos, NVMe-TLS, WireGuard) will
# autoload what they need through the crypto API once the modules
# are present. Users who need a specific algorithm built-in layer
# builtin/security/crypto-algorithms.config or set individual
# =y overrides.
#
# Symbols removed from the kernel in recent releases and
# intentionally NOT set here:
# - CRYPTO_CFB, CRYPTO_OFB (block cipher modes removed)
# - CRYPTO_VMAC (MAC removed)
# - CRYPTO_AES_TI (the generic CRYPTO_AES is constant-time now)
# - CRYPTO_ANSI_CPRNG (legacy X9.31 PRNG removed; use CRYPTO_DRBG)
# - CRYPTO_POLY1305, CRYPTO_CURVE25519, CRYPTO_NHPOLY1305,
#   CRYPTO_GHASH, CRYPTO_HKDF (folded into the lib/crypto forms and
#   auto-selected by their consumers: GCM pulls GHASH, Adiantum
#   pulls NH/Poly1305, fscrypt pulls HKDF).
# CRYPTO_SM3_GENERIC was renamed CRYPTO_SM3 (set below).
#
# Obsolete ciphers behind CRYPTO_USER_API_ENABLE_OBSOLETE (ANUBIS,
# ARC4, KHAZAD, SEED, TEA) are not set: that gate depends on
# crypto-core's af_alg interface, so enable it ad-hoc alongside
# security/crypto-core.config if you need them. Prompt-less
# select-only symbols (CRYPTO_GENIV, CRYPTO_LIB_ARC4,
# CRYPTO_KDF800108_CTR) are not set; their consumers select them.
# DRBG is reached through CRYPTO_DRBG_MENU, not CRYPTO_DRBG directly.
# Architecture-optimised variants like CRYPTO_AES_NI_INTEL live
# under arch/*/crypto/Kconfig and are auto-selected when the
# matching arch is built; they are not restated here.
# See: crypto/Kconfig
# See: crypto/krb5/Kconfig
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/crypto/api-intro.html

#
# Symmetric ciphers
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_AES=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ARIA=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_BLOWFISH=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CAMELLIA=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CAST5=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CAST6=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_SERPENT=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_TWOFISH=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CHACHA20=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_DES=m

#
# Block cipher modes
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CBC=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CTR=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ECB=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CTS=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_XTS=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_GCM=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CCM=m

#
# IV generator
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ESSIV=m

#
# Hashes
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_MD5=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_SHA1=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_SHA256=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_SHA512=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_SHA3=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_SM3=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_BLAKE2B=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_XXHASH=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CRC32=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CRC32C=m

#
# Message authentication codes
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_HMAC=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CMAC=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_XCBC=m

#
# Public-key cryptography
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_RSA=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_DH=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_DH_RFC7919_GROUPS=y
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ECDH=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ECDSA=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ECRDSA=m

#
# Kerberos (used by NFSv4 with RPCSEC_GSS and SMB)
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_KRB5=m

#
# Niche or legacy ciphers and MACs
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_ADIANTUM=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_AEGIS128=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_FCRYPT=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_WP512=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_RMD160=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_STREEBOG=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_LRW=m
CONFIG_CRYPTO_CHACHA20POLY1305=m

#
# Deterministic RNG (DRBG, via the menu symbol) + jitter entropy
#
CONFIG_CRYPTO_DRBG_MENU=y
CONFIG_CRYPTO_JITTERENTROPY=m
